Aim: To apply statistical descriptions and measures of similarity and dissimilarity on the given student academic
performance data.
Tool Used:
WEKA Data Mining Tool
Dataset Used – Iris Dataset:
The Iris dataset is a built-in dataset available in WEKA. It contains 150 instances of iris flowers with numeric
measurements of sepals and petals.
Attributes
1. Sepal Length (numeric)
2. Sepal Width (numeric)
3. Petal Length (numeric)
4. Petal Width (numeric)
5. Class (Iris-setosa, Iris-versicolor, Iris-virginica)
This dataset is suitable because all attributes are numeric, which helps in calculating statistical measures and
distance-based similarity.
Procedure:
Step 1: Open WEKA
 Double click on WEKA Tool
 Click on Explorer
Step 2: Load the Iris Dataset
 Go to Preprocess tab
 Click Open file
 Navigate to: WEKA → data → iris.arff
 Click Open
 The dataset with 150 instances and 5 attributes will be loaded

Step 3: Observe Dataset Information
In the Preprocess tab, observe:
 Relation name: iris
 Number of instances: 150
 Number of attributes: 5

Step 4: Apply Statistical Description
Select each numeric attribute one by one:
(a) Sepal Length
 Click sepal length
 Note: Minimum, Maximum, Mean, Standard Deviation

(b) Sepal Width
 Click sepal width
 Note the statistical values
